reviewText: LOVED this series.  so sad when it ended.  must buy for romantic comedy collectors.  Incredibly funny!
I've watched this so many times I've memorized the dialog and when I'm watching these episodes my participation is very much like the audience participation in The Rocky Horror Picture Show.
I am sad that there was only 2 seasons of this show before it was cancelled ugh....

I thought this was a good show and I bought it for a reasonable price of $5. I thought that Christina Applegate did a great job acting in this...but I bought it because Melissa McCarthy is in it and I think she is a great actor. She is very funny and she looks like an everyday woman.
Christina Applegate is so great in the show. But back to about the DVD. The discs are in great condition, and the case makes it so you don't have to worry about the case banging your DVDs around.
I love this show!  The entire cast is wonderful and hilarious--so sorry that there is only two seasons.
Five stars. Hilariously funny. Love Barry Watson

God I love this TV show, and it kills me that it got cancelled so quickly and it's not even its fault.
The channel wanted to see which shows are people really watching, so they switched up their line up to see if their reality singing competition was causing more people to watch this series just because the show was going to start in thirty minutes or so. So instead of having this okay before or after they changed the day it would play on, and they noticed a big drop in viewing and unfortunately this show was one of the many that soon got the cut.
Such a shame.
Good and funny show but it seemed to get better in season 2 which was sadly also the last of this series.
Cool little show that I failed to catch when it was on the air. Great cast, clever storyline. Second season gets a little stale but worth investing time for some laughs.
Haven't finished the whole thing. But so far it's excellent : )
